      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics must be applied between simulation outputs and experimental measurements, with agreement within defined acceptance bands.",
      "rationale": "Pressure-head predictions agree with experimental measurements within 4.1% RMS across all operating points. Relative hemolysis index predictions fall within the experimental uncertainty band (±15%) for 4 of 5 conditions; the fifth condition shows 17.3% deviation, which is within the expanded uncertainty attributed to blood analogue variability."
